This paper deals with optimizing SPARQL query answering over OWL ontologies, which involves reasoning and knowledge representation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes several optimization techniques, which involve database systems and query processing, making cs.DB (Databases) another likely sub-category. The use of cost-based models and clustering techniques also suggests a connection to machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves software engineering aspects such as implementation and evaluation, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of specialized reasoning tasks and concept hierarchy suggests a connection to programming languages and compilers, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a possible sub-category.
